documentation_summary: DataHub, developed by Acryl Data and LinkedIn, is the leading open-source metadata platform designed to simplify the complexity of data ecosystems. It supports data discovery, observability, and federated governance through an extensible framework. The platform integrates with numerous systems like Kafka, Airflow, MySQL, and more, fostering a massive ecosystem. DataHub's architecture is push-based, allowing for real-time metadata changes and scalability across any organization size. It combines technical, operational, and business metadata for a comprehensive view of data entities and supports automated metadata ingestion. The platform is trusted across various industries for managing sensitive data, documentation, and enhancing data discovery.
